reviews.review: The ultimate Star Wars in every sense of the word, but maybe not for the casual fan.
It is a bit choppy but very entertaining and considering the mess it had to clean up from the last movie it does an admirable job.

A slow revisionist take on starwars that has more incommon with Netflix final space than the orginal starwars saga. Slow plot and nonsensical outcomes shows the zero stakes and reminds one more of starwars christmas special than ep 6
It was a great movie lots of action and surprises

This movie contradicted what what already established in cannon. This movie also undercuts the importance of the original trilogy. The biggest sin was probably bringing back the emperor. Rey was to powerful for the amount of training she has had. The movie also dosnt answers it's own questions and has sever story threads that dont ever get fully realized. I'm disappointed and I hope moving forward we get something fresh and and original.

I really enjoyed it honestly. Don’t care what the critics think or the “hardcore” fans think. I believe they filled the holes in the story that needed to and well as add a good amount of pieces for the fans.

The last Jedi was the death of Star Wars. This was weekend at bernie's, a lifeless & soulless corpse being paraded around as if it was something it certainly was not. 

The best I can say is that it was dull & forgettable. 

At worst, it was a mockery of what Star Wars once was; full of continuity errors, cringe moments, minimal story, no character development & Mary Sue characters. It was like watching a video game of: go to location a, now b, now location c & activate the predictable quick time event. 

For what was claimed to have been & for what should have been the "endgame" of Star Wars, the end of 40 years of cinema, the skywalker story, it was little more than cookie cutter popcorn flick that really shows how lazy, uncaring & predictably boring Disney is now.

In the end, this felt like a quick wrap up of a story that was ruined by the last Jedi & everyone involved just wanted to wash their hands of it & try to pretend this never happened.

The movie was more focused on appealing to the critics of TLJ that they forgot to create a meaningful or even coherent plot. The film spends most of its time retconning TLJ and TFA and trying too hard to distract us with nostalgic scenes of original Star Wars characters and locations. TROS asks questions that it never answers, and introduces new characters that have no purpose while reducing already existing characters to almost nothing. The ending is not uplifting or hopeful despite the beautiful score trying to convince you otherwise. Ironically, after the divisive mess that was TLJ, you will be better off seeing Rian Johnson's Knives Out.
Great overall plot and ending to the saga!! Leaves you with some many questions that leaves you wanting more!!

A fun filled, fast paced film (sometimes too fast) that mostly delivers with fan service (I'm good with that) and fixes many of the Last Jedi's ‘smack in the face' treatment of the fans. Characters are redeemed and story lines are resolved. Some will hate this film, but I believe they would despise anything produced under Kathleen Kennedy. This movie captures the thrill and magic of the original trilogy. I'm seeing it at least two more times this coming week.
